If I had to explain this solve path to a non-engineer in one sentence:

**“It checks whether a repeatedly loaded spring is strong enough, durable enough, and compact enough to be worth building — and if not, exactly what disqualifies it.”**

And if I had to explain the iterative fatigue design path in an even more human way:

**“The computer is auditioning spring candidates and rejecting the ones that are too weak, too long, too unstable, or too impractical.”**

That is why it matters.
